==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Muconic
<hw>Mu*con"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Mu</ets>cic +
ita<ets>conic</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Of, pertaining to,
or designating, an organic acid (<chform>C6H6O4</chform>,
<chname>2-4-hexadienedoic acid</chname>), obtained indirectly from mucic
acid, and somewhat resembling itaconic acid. Various other means of
synthesis have been reported.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mucopurulent</ent>⟦br⟧
